The paper focuses on using deep learning models for skin lesion analysis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of data augmentation is a common technique in machine learning, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of various types of data augmentation, including color and geometric transforms, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of data augmentation on dataset sizes, which could also relate to information retrieval (cs.IR).
